I am always delighted when I can find promise in a new aspirant.<note>CD used Gleig as an intermediary to communicate with Amelia Edwards, who contributed ‘Picking up Terrible Company’ to ‘Tom Tiddler's Ground’. See Pilgrim <hi rend="italic">Letters</hi> 9, p. 455 (To Gleig, 16 September 1861).</note> Pray do me the favor to address the Ghost story to me personally, here. You may rely upon my reading it myself and giving it my best and earliest attention.
